  "title": "AMRI 16-N-0031 sleep1",
  "description": "An overnight EEG-fMRI pilot study examining sleep physiology and brain activity during spontaneous arousals. Approximately 20 subjects underwent two consecutive nights of simultaneous EEG and fMRI recording (~8 hours per night) with 8 randomized arousal events per night. This dataset serves as the foundational pilot for a larger follow-up study (sleep2) and provides multimodal neuroimaging data during sleep stages and arousal transitions.",
  "methods_description": "Overnight EEG-fMRI simultaneous recording performed over two consecutive nights (~8 hours per night). Subjects were aroused at random intervals 8 times during each night. Data collection conducted at the Advanced MRI section, LFMI, NINDS, NIH during 2016-2017.",
